          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "category": "DHL Delivery",
            "tags": "country estimates",
            "question": "How long to my country?",
            "answer": "<p>As a guide: KSA ~4–5d, UK/US ~5d, AU/CA ~6d. Some routes are faster; customs may add time. We’ll keep you updated via your tracking link.</p>",
            "sources": ""
          }
        },
        "i3": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "category": "DHL Delivery",
            "tags": "tracking dates,reliability,eta",
            "question": "About DHL’s tracking dates",
            "answer": "<p>DHL’s dates are estimates and can shift with flights or customs. If your parcel goes beyond your window, message us and we’ll escalate with DHL right away.</p>",
            "sources": ""
          }
        },
        "i4": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "category": "DHL Delivery",
            "tags": "exception,customs,hold",
            "question": "What does “Exception” mean?",
            "answer": "<p>It’s a temporary stop—often a customs check or local delivery event. You usually don’t need to do anything. We monitor these and will update you. If an item can’t clear, we’ll offer a reship, split shipment, or a refund.</p>",
